 ## Unreleased

+### Added
+
+- Added `App::negation_prefix(std::string)` method to configure an automatic
+  negation prefix for boolean flags (default: empty, opt-in). When set to
+  `"no-"`, every `add_flag("--verbose", ...)` call automatically registers
+  `--no-verbose` as the negated form, setting the flag to `false`.
+
 ## Version 2.6.2
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index 823402c..adbfa9f 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -389,6 +389,25 @@ while in C++11 mode you'll need to use `.add_flag_function` if you want a
 callback function. The function will be given the number of times the flag was
 passed. You can throw a relevant `CLI::ParseError` to signal a failure.

+#### Negation prefix
+
+You can configure an automatic negation prefix so that every boolean flag
+gets a corresponding `--no-<name>` variant registered automatically:
+
+```cpp
+CLI::App app{"My App"};
+app.negation_prefix("no-");       // enable auto-negation with "no-" prefix
+
+bool verbose{false};
+app.add_flag("--verbose", verbose, "Enable verbose output");
+// --verbose   → verbose = true
+// --no-verbose → verbose = false
+```
